<section xmlns="http://xml.house.gov/schemas/uslm/1.0" style="-uslm-lc:I80" id="id52c3aecf-3a70-11f1-9e0c-dcbb1364dae6" identifier="/us/usc/t28/s1872"><num value="1872">§ 1872.</num><heading> Issues of fact in Supreme Court</heading><content>
<p style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">In all original actions at law in the Supreme Court against citizens of the United States, issues of fact shall be tried by a jury.</p>
</content><sourceCredit id="id52c3aed0-3a70-11f1-9e0c-dcbb1364dae6">(<ref href="/us/act/1948-06-25/ch646">June 25, 1948, ch. 646</ref>, <ref href="/us/stat/62/953">62 Stat. 953</ref>.)</sourceCredit>
<notes type="uscNote" id="id52c3aed1-3a70-11f1-9e0c-dcbb1364dae6">
<note style="-uslm-lc:I74" topic="historicalAndRevision" id="id52c3aed2-3a70-11f1-9e0c-dcbb1364dae6"><heading class="centered smallCaps">Historical and Revision Notes</heading><p style="-uslm-lc:I21" class="indent0">Based on title 28, U.S.C., 1940 ed., § 343 (<ref href="/us/act/1911-03-03/ch231/s235">Mar. 3, 1911, ch. 231, § 235</ref>, <ref href="/us/stat/36/1156">36 Stat. 1156</ref>).</p>
<p style="-uslm-lc:I21" class="indent0">Changes were made in phraseology.</p>
</note>
